<TITLE> No pressure to resign: ACC commissioner </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 4 (bdnews24.com) - TThe government was not pressing members of the Anticorruption Commission to resign, said a commissioner on Sunday. "There is no such pressure," Habibur Rahman said answering reporters' queries as he left work for the day. "It is the government's will whether we resign or not. However, we will serve in the ACC as long as we can," he said. Queried about the resignation of ACC chairman Hasan Mashhud Chowdhury, he said, " The media was making too much speculation on the reconstitution of the commission." "All including constables and commissioners have to resign to reconstitute the ACC. Is it possible?" He also criticised the past caretaker government, saying, "The former government did not help the commission to perform its job well." b
